# Shell script header (two sections)

When editing any `*.sh` file in this repo, update **both** header sections at the top (newest changelog entry first).

## Section 1 — version changelog

Immediately after the shebang, add a new top line:

```bash
# YYYY.MM.DD - v. MAJOR.MINOR[.PATCH] - brief what changed
```

- Use today's date (`YYYY.MM.DD`).
- Bump version from the current top entry.
- One short line: what changed and why.
- Do not edit or reorder older changelog lines.
- `print_version_banner` and `_script_header.sh` read the **first** matching line — keep the new entry on top.

## Section 2 — script description block

After the full changelog (oldest entry last), add or update a short description block:

```bash
# 2026.07.15 - v. 1.7 - ...
# 2026.07.15 - v. 1.6 - ...
# 2020.11.27 - v. 0.1 - initial release
#
# git-pull.sh
#
# Pull github-bin from GitHub; install scripts to ${profile_location_dir:-$HOME}/bin.
#
```

- Description block comes **after all changelog lines**, before the code.
- Add a description block to new scripts and sourced helpers (`_git-bin-common.sh`, etc.).
- Sourced helpers need Section 1 changelog too (they have no `print_version_banner`).

## Also update when touched

- `_script_header.sh` / `_script_footer.sh` — own changelog if modified.
- Commit and push to `master` unless the user says otherwise.
